               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-199-person1115">
                  SAMUEL 
                  LLOYD
               <interp inst="t18280529-199-person1115" type="surname" value="LLOYD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-199-person1115" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-199-person1115" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was in the employ of George Cottam and Samuel Hallen; I have the care of their premises - they are <rs id="t18280529-199-viclabel1110" type="occupation">agricultural implement makers</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-199-victim1113 t18280529-199-viclabel1110"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-199-victim1114 t18280529-199-viclabel1110"></join>. On the 20th of May, I sent him to Mr. Burys' for some wire; I told him to fetch some paper to put it into - he went into the store-room - I thought him a long time - I went to look, and saw his hand in his trousers pocket - I followed him out some distance, went up and said, "Tom, you are wanted;" he came back, and went up to Mr. Cottam; I said, "Tom, you have been doing wrong:" he turned round and said, "Don't;" I said "It is too late;" Mr. Cottam came round and took this parcel of brass from him; he gave no account of it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-199-person1116">
                  JOHN 
                  WYATT
               <interp inst="t18280529-199-person1116" type="surname" value="WYATT"></interp>
